Ascalaphus and Ialmenus were guides, Begot by Mars upon Astyoche.
The towns of Phocis, Crissa, Panopea, And Cyparissus, Python, and Daulis, And on the brook of Cepliisus Lilæa, And Anemoria, and Hyampolis, And other towns o' th' bank of Cephisus, Made ready forty good ships for the seas, Ruled by Schedius and Epistraphus The sons of Iphitus Naubolides.
The Locrians the lesser Ajax led, Of King Oileus the valiant son.
(For he was lower more than by the head Than t' other Ajax, son of Telamon)
A linen armour he wore on his breast.
