But then the ships Atrides furnished.
The men of Helis, and Buprasium, And all the ground enclos'd by Hyrmine, Myrsinus, Olene, Alisium, Amongst them all put forty ships to sea, Led by Amphimachus and Thalpius, Diores, and Polyxenus, the son Of martial Agasthenes, and then Ten good ships were commanded by each one.
Dulichium, and th' isles Echinades, Sent forty ships.
Messes commander went
The son of Phyleus, who for his ease Liv'd from his father there in discontent.
