Ay me, said he, what now shall I do here ?
Though many be the foes, 'tis ill to fly, But yet, since Jove saves all the rest by flight, It would be worse if I alone should die.
But why dispute I, when I ought to fight ?
None but a coward from the fight will run.
But he that honour loves will stand his ground,
And be content with what he cannot shun, Whether it be to give or take a wound.
While thus Ulysses argued in his mind, Hector was near him, and enclosed him had With targetiers before him and behind, Whereof they had no reason to be glad.
