Nestor to Troy had with him brought this cup.
Another scarce could lift it from the table
When fill'd with wine;
though he to take it up, Old as he was, and easily was able.
And in the same the woman made the drink, With goat's-milk cheese, and white flour sprinkled o'er, And left it on the board full to the brink.
