And now the meat in messes some divided, Others the lusty wine were tempering, And by a squire the singer in was guided, And at a pillar in the midst made sit.
Ulysses half a chine of pork and fat Cuts off, and in the squire's hands putteth it, And said unto him, Give the singer that;
