They have no courts of counsel, nor of right.
On high huge hills themselves they entertain, And in their rocky bellies pass the night.
Each man gives law to his own wife and brood:
Nor do they much for one another care.
Before the port an isle lies clad with wood, Not very near, nor from it very far.
Wild goats in great abundance were therein :
Because there dwelt no man that might them kill, Nor wretched hunters ever enter in, To tire themselves running from hill to hill.
