And now ourselves we prostrate at your feet, Hoping for some good thing as visitants, Such as all men have commonly thought meet;
Or, for the Gods' sake, as to suppliants.
As suppliants we before you here do lie, With whom, and strangers, Jove still goes along;
He is the God of hospitality, To punish whosoever does them wrong.
Thus I.
