But when it came up to his brain,
Then spake I to him gentle words and soft:
Cyclops, since you my name desire to know, I'll tell it you, and on your word rely.
My name is Noman, all men call me so, My father, mother, and my company.
To which he soon and sadly made reply, Noman, I'll eat you last, none shall outlive you Of all that are here of your company;
And that's the gift I promised to give you.
And having said, he laid himself along With bended neck, sleeping and vomiting Gobbets of human flesh, and wine among, All he before had eaten uttering.
