The rest that will may go, and, morning spread, Drive forth the swine, which is their business.
Meanwhile let us sit here, and drink and chat,
And stories of our sad adventures tell;
For much contentment there is ev'n in that, To them that suffer'd have and come off well.
But to my story now.
An isle there is Under the tropic of the sun, not great, Call'd Syria, but very fertile 'tis, Well stor'd with kine, and sheep, and wine and wheat, Where famine never enter'd, nor disease Amongst the people.
When a man was aged, Dian' and Phœbus made him die with ease, And gentle shafts the pain of death assuaged.
